cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning techniques for video object segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel approach using guided convolutional neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of attention mechanisms and independent algorithms, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with motion features, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper's focus on video object segmentation could also be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics).
